    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Twentieth century Japanese printmaking movement that was based on the artists' personal involvement in all stages of print production as opposed to the teamwork style of traditional "ukiyo-e" print production. The term literally means "creative print." </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
